        • name

          String name
          The name of the data model. This is not used internally; it is only here in case an external class wants this dataset to have a name.
           

        • variables

          List<E> variables
          The list of variables. These correspond columnwise to the columns of data.
           

        • dataBox

          DataBox dataBox
          The container storing the data. Rows are cases; columns are variables. The order of columns is coordinated with the order of variables in getVariables().
           

        • selection

          Set<E> selection
          The set of selected variables.
           

        • caseIds

          Map<K,V> caseIds
          Case ID's. These are strings associated with some or all of the cases of the dataset.
           

        • multipliers

          Map<K,V> multipliers
          A map from cases to case multipliers. If a case is not in the domain of this map, its case multiplier is by default 1. This is the number of repetitions of the case in the dataset. The sample size is obtained by summing over these multipliers.
           

        • knowledge

          IKnowledge knowledge
          The knowledge associated with this data.
           

        • outputDelimiter

          char outputDelimiter
          The character used as a delimiter when the dataset is printed.

        • readObject

          private void readObject(ObjectInputStream s)
                 throws IOException,
                        ClassNotFoundException
          Adds semantic checks to the default deserialization method. This method must have the standard signature for a readObject method, and the body of the method must begin with "s.defaultReadObject();". Other than that, any semantic checks can be specified and do not need to stay the same from version to version. A readObject method of this form may be added to any class, even if Tetrad sessions were previously saved out using a version of the class that didn't include it. (That's what the "s.defaultReadObject();" is for. See J. Bloch, Effective Java, for help.

      • Serialized Fields

        • variables

          SortedSet<E> variables
          The set of variable names this knowledge is over.

        • tierMap

          Map<K,V> tierMap
          This is a representation of the temporal tiers, a map from Strings to Integers. Each variable name is mapped to exactly one tier (an Integer). To determine whether an edge v1 --> v2 is forbidden by the tiers, find tierMap(v1) and tierMap(v2); if tierMap(v1) > tierMap(v2), the edge is forbidden by tiers. If either tierMap(v1) or tierMap(v2) is null, the edge is not forbidden by tiers, and if tierMap(v1) <= tierMap(v2), the edge is not forbidden by tiers. In this representation, in order to get all the varNames of a given tier, iterate through the domain of the map and observe which elements map to the Integer value of that tier.
           

        • requiredEdges

          Set<E> requiredEdges
          This is the set of edges explicitly required by the user

          Note: Should really be called "explicitlyRequiredEdges" (can't change though).

           

        • allRequiredEdges

          Set<E> allRequiredEdges
          This is the set of all edges that are required, including edges explicitly required and required by groups.
           

        • explicitlyForbiddenEdges

          Set<E> explicitlyForbiddenEdges
          This is the set of edges explicitly forbidden by the user.
           

        • expicitlyNotForbidden

          Set<E> expicitlyNotForbidden
          This is the set of edges explicitly not forbidden. Only one of this and\ ExplicitlyForbiddenEdges can be non-null.

        • requiredCommonCauses

          Set<E> requiredCommonCauses
          This is the set of required common causes.
           

        • forbiddenCommonCauses

          Set<E> forbiddenCommonCauses
          This is the set of forbidden common causes.
           

        • tiersForbiddenWithin

          Set<E> tiersForbiddenWithin
          True iff tier 0 consists of exogenous variables, so that all edges among tier 0 variables are forbidden.
           

        • knowledgeGroups

          List<E> knowledgeGroups
          The knowledge groups, this contains all the grouping information.
           

        • defaultToKnowledgeLayout

          boolean defaultToKnowledgeLayout
          When the graph for this knowledge is displayed, it defauls to the knowledge layout if this is true.
           

        • lagged

          boolean lagged

        • readObject

          private void readObject(ObjectInputStream s)
                 throws IOException,
                        ClassNotFoundException
          Adds semantic checks to the default deserialization method. This method must have the standard signature for a readObject method, and the body of the method must begin with "s.defaultReadObject();". Other than that, any semantic checks can be specified and do not need to stay the same from version to version. A readObject method of this form may be added to any class, even if Tetrad sessions were previously saved out using a version of the class that didn't include it. (That's what the "s.defaultReadObject();" is for. See J. Bloch, Effective Java, for help.
